"Application Module" - "Root Module" (exe in a .NET)- Routed - When you have a feature in your application that stands on it's own. - For example, you want to add a feature to the application that lets users retrieve and print their ID cards. - We need to talk about routing a bit, but you'll see how this works.- Domain - Responsible for a business are of the application - provides services and maybe components that can be used across the app- Shared Modules - UI (Widgets) - Components that are shared across the application - Application Cross-Cutting - Validation stuff, selectors, actions, etc.
